[normal]4.20
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Defined benefit pensions are becoming increasingly costly fo
[normal]r all the remaining employers who offer such a scheme because of conditions in the financial markets, including very low gilt yields. 
[normal]T
[normal]he proportion of companies that closed their defined benefit schemes to existing employees climbed to 31 per cent in 2012
[normal]. This is an increase of more than a third from 23 per cent in 2011
[normal] (Source: NAPF)
[normal].
