[normal]5.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The long-term commercial agreement ensures that Royal Mail services 
[normal]will continue to be
[normal] available through all post offices in the future.
[normal] In January 2012, then Postal Services Minister Edward Davey said:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“Concerns people had about the Post Office becoming independent from Royal Mail were always misplaced as that separation is part of our cu
[normal]re, but the ten year deal struck between Royal Mail and the Post Office will give subpostmasters and others greater confidence.”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In Post O
[normal]ffice Ltd’s Network Report 2013, it said that there has been “greater stability over recent years than has been the c
[normal]ase for the previous quarter of a century.”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is in both Royal Mail and Post Office Ltd’s interest to ensure a strong, comprehensive post office network. Combined with Government funding of the Post Office and allowing Royal Mail to access external capit
[normal]al, separation will safeguard the future of both companies and the commercial relationship between them. 
[normal]Separation has also given Post Office management greater freedom to focus on its customers and growing its revenue base.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Continued
[normal] transformation of R
[normal]oyal Mail would result in more business – particularly from the growing parcels market - going through post offices, and a stronger post office network. At the same time, the Post Office Network Transformation programme will result in longer opening hours 
[normal]at post offices, and greater flexibility for postal services users. This will allow Royal Mail’s customers greater access to parcels services and benefit both companies. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Royal 
[normal]Mail, working with the Post Office, will later this year 
[normal]launch 
[normal]the UK’s large
[normal]st ‘click and collect’ network to support online shopping growth by providing greater choice of convenient parcel delivery options for online retailers and their customers.
[normal] 
[normal]Post Office has the largest retail network in the UK, making branches the ideal loc
[normal]ations to provide convenient, secure parcel collection facilities. 99 per cent of the population lives within three miles of a Post Office branch. Around 10,500 Post Offices will be taking part in the initiative which will enable online retailers to offer 
[normal]shoppers the opportunity to order items for collection at their local 
[normal]post office 
[normal]branch.
