[normal]Heritage[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]5.7
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Royal Mail is proud of its heritage. It is one of the best 
[normal]known and trusted 
[normal]brands in the country. There would be no incentive to rebrand or change its iconic visual symbols like post boxes. 
[normal]To do so would require very significant expenditure and 
[normal]would 
[normal]risk alienating our customers.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.8
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Sovereign will continue to approve all 
[normal]stamp issues. The Secretary of State has the power to ensure her image
[normal], and the image of subsequent Monarchs,
[normal] appears on stamps. This process is safeguarded in the Postal Services Act 2011 (Section 62 – “UK postage stamps bearing an image of Her Majesty”
[normal] a
[normal]nd Section 10, Interpretation Act 1978 – “References to the Sovereign”
[normal]).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.9
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Royal Mail established the B
[normal]ritish 
[normal]P
[normal]ostal 
[normal]M
[normal]useum and 
[normal]A
[normal]rchive
[normal] in 2004 to manage the public records of The Royal Mail Archive. Stamps form part of the public record and could only be s
[normal]old with the agreement of the National Archive and other Government bodies. The long-term funding agreements signed between Royal Mail 
[normal]and the BPMA will continue beyond privatisation.
[normal] Royal Mail has also gifted Calthorpe House, the site of the BPMA’s new s
[normal]torage and exhibition centre, to the museum.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Government’s recent reforms have put Royal Mail back in a position to compete and grow. The transfer of the 
[normal]to the Government of the Group’s pension liabilities for pre-1 April 2012 service and 
[normal]certain assets relating to the Royal Mail Pension Plan,
[normal] and reform of the regulatory framework, alongside an acceleration in the company’s transformation programme, have returned Royal Mail to profit. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The challenge is now to maintain this positive moment
[normal]um. 
[normal]Privatisation will allow the company to innovate, invest, improve our services, win new business, deliver the high quality Universal Service, and continue to be 
[normal]a very substantial employer in the UK
[normal].
